The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 01, 2004 				 Mahindra fourth-quarter net zooms
 OUR BUREAUX  On fast track 																								May 31: Tractor major Mahindra amp; Mahindra Ltd (M amp;M) has posted a 199 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 145.64 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 48.68 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.																								Total income increased to Rs 1,545 crore in the reporting quarter against Rs 1,142.48 crore in the year-ago period.																								Net profits for the last fiscal stood at Rs 348.54 crore compared with Rs 145.53 crore a year earlier. 																								Gross sales and income from operations last fiscal was Rs 5,914.5 crore as against Rs 4,517.1 crore in the previous year. In dollar terms, M amp;Ms gross sales and income crossed $1 billion to touch $1.34 billion compared with $950 million in 2002-03. 																								Net sales and operating income in 2003-04 increased 33 per cent to Rs 4,959.1 crore compared with Rs 3,732.1 crore in the previous fiscal. 																								The board of directors today recommended a dividend of 90 per cent (Rs 9 per share).																								The companys automotive division recorded a 35 per cent growth in volumes at 1,17,386 units (including three wheelers) during the year. 																								Last fiscal, sale of utility vehicle rose 34 per cent to 91,434 units from 68,852 units in the previous year. 																								The company is optimistic about the current financial year. The robust growth seen in the economy augurs well for the automotive and the tractor industries, M amp;M said. 																								With the new government taking charge, there could be a shift in priorities and the announcements so far point towards increased investments in the agriculture and infrastructure sectors. This would bring consequential benefits to M amp;M as the basic thrust of the companys business is towards the rural and the semi-urban markets, the company said in a statement.																								Hind Petro posts profit																								Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 527.05 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 634.12 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. 																								Total income (net of excise) has increased to Rs 14,700.9 crore from Rs 13,896.94 crore in the year-ago period.																								The company has posted a net profit of Rs 1,903.94 crore in the last financial year against Rs 1,537.36 crore in the previous financial year. Total income (net of excise) rose to Rs 51,897.05 crore compared with Rs 48,956.96 crore in 2002-03.																								The board has recommended a final dividend of 160 per cent in addition to the interim dividend of 60 per cent paid during the year. Punjab Tractors																								Punjab Tractors Ltd has posted a lower net profit of Rs 42.02 crore in the last financial year ended March 31, 2004 against Rs 43.12 crore in the previous fiscal.																								The board has recommended a dividend of 45 per cent for the year, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today.																								Total income during the period under review rose to Rs 603.3 crore from Rs 551.1 crore in the previous financial year, the statement said.																								Net profit for the fourth quarter of the last fiscal stood at Rs 16.72 crore compared with Rs 8.32 crore in the year-ago period. 																								Total income during the reporting quarter stood at Rs 186.6 crore against Rs 115 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.
